2. Test Scores #1
Write a program that dynamically allocates an array large enough to hold a user
defined number of test scores. Once all score are entered, the array should be
passed to a function that sorts them in ascending order. Another function should
be called that calculates the average score. The program should display the sorted list
of scores and averages with appropriate headings. Use pointer notation rather than array
notatiohn whenever possible.

Input Validation: Do not accepth negative numbers for test scores.
